          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-09-20 15:45:19.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Lai Siyao",
          "email": "lai.siyao@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-08-28 07:55:45.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1976 oi: check index node before recycle empty leaf",
        "message": "LU-1976 oi: check index node before recycle empty leaf\n\nThere may be multiple threads trying to shrink the same OI index\nnode to recycle different empty OI leaf nodes concurrently, and\nsomeone may enlarged or split the index node before the threads\nshrinking the index node to recycle the empty OI leaf nodes.\nThese concurrent OI index node modifications will change leaf\nnode position in the index node. So before shrinking the index\nnode, we need to check and adjust related frame pointer to avoid\nto shrink the index node improperly as to crash the memory.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I5d5d2fc19e56ab7424ae659554309782fcd136ef\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
